rature, art, and culture are little known in countries where Portuguese is not spoken. But within Brazil, contemporary artists and writers are creating a culture that is both cosmopolitan and inclusive of the nation’s diverse regions, customs, and dialects. Becoming Brazil includes works by canonical twentieth-century Brazilian writers, innovative contemporary authors, and new voices, many of them in translation for the first time. The volume also includes stunning black and white images by Brazilian photographer Sebastião Salgado.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2021) 7aLITERARY COLLECTIONS / Caribbean & Latin American.2bisacsh1 aAlphonsus, João, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAzevedo, Carlito, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeber, Bruna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBecker, Eric M. B., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBrum, Eliane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCalixto, Fabiano, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDucaso, Ruth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEvaristo, Conceição, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFernando Abreu, Caio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrança Castro, Marcílio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFux, Jacques, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGuimarães Rosa, João, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHatoum, Milton, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIvo, Lêdo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKersley, Sarah Rebecca, 